21/04/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police have arrested a Slovenian citizen suspected of genocide committed in Srebrenica at the end of the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict, media reported on Tuesday (April 20th). Franc Kos was detained late Monday near the town of Osijek, based on an international arrest warrant issued by Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). He will spend 45 days in custody, pending extradition to BiH. Authorities say that as a member of the Bosnian Serb Army, Kos participated in killing Bosniaks in the enclave in July 1995. Born in Slovenia, he also holds Bosnian citizenship. (RTS, Vecernji List, BHRT, RTRS - 20/04/10)
